value.title: Coronavirus: Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people
value.excerpt: Italy's prime minister has said at least 16 million people are now under lock-down in Lombardy region and also in 14 provinces until early April. Wedding and funerals are also suspended under the mandatory quarantine.
